{"id":"1403.3608","submitter":"V.P.J. Jacobs","authors":"V.P.J. Jacobs, S.J.G. Vandoren, H.T.C. Stoof","title":"Holographic interaction effects on transport in Dirac semimetals","comments":"Published version, with additional discussion on inter- and intraband\n  contributions and Drude peak. 7 pages, 5 figures","journal-ref":"Phys. Rev. B. 90, 045108 (2014)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevB.90.045108","report-no":null,"categories":"cond-mat.str-el hep-th","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Strongly interacting Dirac semimetals are investigated using a holographic\nmodel especially geared to compute the single-particle correlation function for\nthis case, including both interaction effects and nonzero temperature. We\ncalculate the (homogeneous) electrical conductivity at zero chemical potential,\nand show that it consists of two contributions. The interband contribution\nscales as a power law either in frequency or in temperature for low frequency.\nThe precise power is related to a critical exponent of the dual holographic\ntheory, which is a parameter in the model. On top of that we find for nonzero\ntemperatures a Drude peak corresponding to intraband transitions. A behavior\nsimilar to Coulomb interactions is recovered as a special limiting case.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 14 Mar 2014 15:29:12 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 13 Jun 2014 10:21:19 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 10 Jul 2014 15:57:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-07-11"}
